### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api


### ✅ Register a New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "John Doe",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### ✅ Login User
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

### Capture the token from the login response (Rest Client feature)
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### ✅ Test Protected Route (Example: Projects)
# This uses the token captured automatically from the login request above
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json